President Muhammadu Buhari has re-appointed Dr. Chikwe Ihekweazu as Director General of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). The NCDC announcement the re-appointment in a statement posted on its twitter page on Monday. “We are proud to announce that our Director General, Dr Chikwe Ihekweazu has been re-appointed into office by President Muhammadu Buhari,” the statement read. “The NCDC remains committed to protecting the health of Nigerians, under the leadership of Dr Ihekweazu.”